formatted_address: 469 Bukit Batok West Ave 9, #01-15 West Hawker Centre, Singapore 650469
name: Huang Chao Teochew Noodle House

reviews.text:
I had the signature noodle and the noodles with vinegar, tomato and chilli sauce (this combi is a must have).

It is quite tasty and worth it for the price; when add mince meat they actually add quite a big portion.

Worth a try!

Similar to other reviews, the queue process and service is super slow. There was no queue when I ordered a bowl of noodles, and I ended up waiting for 20 mins because they were busy doing takeaways. They prioritise takeaways rather than a customer waiting before them.

But gotta admit that their noodles were very chewy and seasoning was on point. But it's really not worth a 20 mins wait.
The fish ball and fish cake are Q and taste good, enough fish content. The dry noodle gravy taste is pretty common, the soup is nice

Compared to some of the other reviews, my experience was rather positive on the whole. The taking my order was cheerful and polite, and I did not have to wait long as I was early. The $4 bowl of dry fishball noodles tasted pretty good (noodles a bit "QQ", had sufficient ingredients), and the biggish bowl of soup had a light tasty "ti por" flavour.
Tried their signature noodle(black sauce, thin noodle, $6). Meat portion is slightly big. Soup base and noodle is acceptable. Expect to wait 10-15mins. Overall 8/10.

vicinity: 469 Bukit Batok West Avenue 9, #01-15 West Hawker Centre
